🖥️ Steps to Install Docker Desktop on Windows
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Check prerequisites
---------------------------
Windows 10 (Pro/Enterprise, build 19045 or later) or Windows 11.

Enable WSL 2 (Windows Subsystem for Linux) — you already have the Microsoft Learn guide open, which walks you through setting up Linux with WSL.

Ensure virtualization is enabled in BIOS.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Download Docker Desktop 

From the Docker Docs installation page (the tab you have open), download the installer for Windows. -> https://docs.docker.com/desktop/setup/install/windows-install?utm_source=copilot.com

Run the installer

Double-click the .exe file.

During setup, select WSL 2 backend (recommended) instead of Hyper-V if prompted.

Complete setup

Restart your system if required.

Launch Docker Desktop from the Start menu.

The first time it runs, Docker will finalize integration with WSL 2.

Verify installation

Open PowerShell or Command Prompt and run:

bash
docker --version
docker run hello-world
If you see the “Hello from Docker!” message, you’re good to go.
