Here’s a clear checklist to enable WSL 2 on Windows before installing Docker Desktop. This ensures Docker runs smoothly with Linux containers:

01
Enable WSL Feature
Windows Subsystem for Linux must be turned on before installing Docker.

Open PowerShell as Administrator

Run: dism.exe /online /enable-feature /featurename:Microsoft-Windows-Subsystem-Linux /all /norestart

Wait for confirmation message

02
Enable Virtual Machine Platform
WSL 2 requires virtualization support.

Still in PowerShell (Admin)

Run: dism.exe /online /enable-feature /featurename:VirtualMachinePlatform /all /norestart

Restart your computer after this step

03
Install WSL Update
WSL 2 needs the latest kernel update package.

Download from Microsoft site

Go to: https://aka.ms/wsl2kernel

Install the MSI package

04
Set WSL 2 as Default
Ensure new Linux distributions use WSL 2.

Open PowerShell

Run: wsl --set-default-version 2

Verify with: wsl --list --verbose

05
Install a Linux Distribution
Docker Desktop integrates with Linux distros via WSL.
